        <HEADING SUBTYPE="2">Family and Relationships</HEADING>
        <FAMILY>
            <FAMILYMEMBER RELATION="FATHER">
                <CHRONSTRUCT><CHRONPROSE>Father: <NAME>John Edwards</NAME></CHRONPROSE> <DATERANGE FROM="1808-04-29" TO="1866-12-22">(29 April 1808 – 22 Decembe 1866)</DATERANGE></CHRONSTRUCT>
               <P>Born in Edinburgh, Scotland, in 1808, John Edwards was a Baptist clergyman and pastor in Clarence, ON. He married Sarah Plimsoll (1816-1907) in 1839, a few years after she immigrated to Canada. They had several children together, at least four of whom lived to adulthood. John died in Port Hope, ON in 1866, survived by his wife.</P>
            </FAMILYMEMBER>
            <FAMILYMEMBER RELATION="MOTHER">
                <CHRONSTRUCT><CHRONPROSE>Mother: <NAME>Sarah Plimsoll</NAME></CHRONPROSE> <DATERANGE FROM="1816-12-06" TO="1907-05-03">(6 December 1816 – 3 May 1907)</DATERANGE></CHRONSTRUCT>
               <P>Sarah was born in 1816 in Plymouth, England. She immigrated to Canada 1834, and in 1839 married Reverend John Edwards (1808-1866). Several of their children died in infancy, but at least four lived to adulthood. Sarah died in 1907 in Truro, NS.</P>
            </FAMILYMEMBER>
